bio:
Aside from his professional and political service to his community, Martín has been active as a volunteer and activist in many other roles in his community, including service in the following organizations/committees:

National Hispanic Caucus of State Legislators Chair of Criminal Justice Committee (2016-present)
Board of Hispanic Caucus Chairs, Treasurer (2015-present);
ASU Los Diablos Latino Alumni Association Board of Directors (2001-2016);
Maryvale Village Planning Committee representing Phoenix Council District #7 – appointed by Phoenix City Council (2009-2016)’
West Phoenix Revitalization Community Advisory Board – appointed by Phoenix City Council (2009-present);
National Association of Latino Elected and Appointed Officials (2011-present);
Los Abogados Hispanic Bar Association of AZ Board of Directors (2009-2013); Civil Rights Committee (2008-2013), Chair of Legislative Committee (2009-2011), Chair of Scholarship Committee (2012);
St. Vincent de Paul School Advisory Board (2009-2013)
